
/etc/pyca/[configs] <-- configuration
/etc/httpd/conf.d/pyca <-- web configuration
[/etc/cron.hourly/pyca <-- ? ca-cycle]
/usr/bin/[executables] <-- executables
/usr/sbin/[root executables] <-- root executables
/usr/share/pyca <-- web
/usr/share/doc/pyca-XXXXX <-- documentation
[/var/lib/pyca/certs <-- ?]
/usr/lib/python2.4/site-packages/pycalib <-- library
[or perhaps /usr/local/pyca/pylib ... ]



user caadmin [caadmin] <-- manage CAs
user MailDaemon [daemon] <-- receive and process requests
user wwwUser <-- user running the web server
ErrorLog <-- Log File instead of common apache log

Require MTA



